race.description: Gippsland Racing 'The Best Turf On Earth' Handicap
race.comment: The promising MAGNABELLE ROYALE (9) won three jumpouts and impressed winning a Dunkeld Maiden easily on debut, bet $2.70. This is a step up, but she gives every impression it's winnable with the extra fitness and learning. ASMITA (15) opened this campaign finding one too good at Moe in stronger. She's in a top yard and has more up the sleeve. A live chance to go one better. WARRIOR SMILE (5) resumes for a top barn and has been sharp at the jumpouts. He's been gelded and has a neat miss at Stakes level in the form. Has to be considered. THE WIZARD KING (6) pushed forward from a wide draw and was prominent for a long way before fading beaten 2.7L at Geelong. Maps to advantage and has been unlucky a couple of times this preparation. Each way claims. FOREVER WITH NED (8) has been well prepared for her return and was beaten far in town when last seen. Has placed 2/2 fresh and keep onside.
